Eastern Cape police are investigating a case of murder after the body of a police officer was found inside a burnt vehicle on Sunday. The vehicle, belonging to 36-yearold Constable Vuyo Matshisi, is believed to have been hijacked in Port Elizabeth. His body was found burnt beyond recognition.For the full story get a copy of the Dispatch or subscribe to our e-Edition for the complete newspaper with jobs, classifieds, crosswords, TV schedules and back editions.